 aspired to join an investment team and thanks to my experience on the graduate programme i now work in the china equities team as an investment analyst investment analysts need to have a deep understanding of the sector my rotations in regional equities and the fixed income team in taipei gave me great insight into the sectors i now specialise in such as commodities and paper and china ipps independent power producers working in taipei also provided me with the chance to understand the strategies of different regions and how teams in different offices communicate and collaborate around the world in their daytoday work besides my professional career work also gives me opportunities to get involved in community life i joined the dragon boat team during my graduate training and participated in kids read volunteering during my time in taipei one piece of advice i would give to anyone applying to our graduate programmes is to make full use of all the interviews and interactions to discover what will be best for you ask questions listen to what the answers are and find out if there is a fit between hsbc and you continue exploring our people related programmes our people related programmes william graduate analyst global asset management – london uk learning to understand our clients shows me how we help people save up for life events retirements and other important milestones read williams story shaan strategist global multi asset global asset management – london uk hsbc invests in your career and aims for you to be challenged at all times mentors and buddies point you in the right direction and help broaden your knowledge of the wider business read shaans story view all employee stories programme key information description more information global asset management internship for university undergraduate duration  weeks areas retail banking and wealth management this week internship offers penultimate year degree students the opportunity to build their knowledge in the p